24/06/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Zagreb hosted a regional energy summit on Sunday (June 24th), attended by the presidents of Croatia, Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Macedonia, Montenegro, Romania, Serbia and Russia, representatives of the Greek and Slovenian governments, and a delegation from the European Commission.
The focus was on problems related to energy supplies.
A number of bilateral meetings among participants were also held on the sidelines of the event.
(HRT, Index.hr - 24/06/07)
